  "bio_raw": "Md. Abedullah is a Lecturer of Bangla Language and Literature with extensive experience teaching at leading private universities in Bangladesh, including Green University of Bangladesh, Uttara University and Daffodil International University. He has taught multiple undergraduate courses, supervised large cohorts of students and contributed to curriculum development under Outcome-Based Education (OBE) frameworks aligned with national standards. His academic work focuses on Bangla literature, media, and cultural studies, with particular attention to the relationship between literature, digital media, and political discourse. He is currently pursuing a PhD at Jahangirnagar University. His research has been published in peer-reviewed journals and presented at national conferences. In addition to his academic work, he is actively engaged in creative writing and theatre, integrating interdisciplinary perspectives into his teaching and research practice.",
  "stated_interests": [
    "Novel Studies, Short Story Studies, Twentieth-Century Literature, Literary History, Literature and History."
  ],
  "education": [
    {
      "raw": "Education\nPhD\n(Ongoing), Department of Bangla, Jahangirnagar University.\nTitle:\nAutobiographical Writings in Bangladesh: Society, Culture and Politics from the Perspective of Political Figures\nMaster’s, Department of Bangla\n, Jahangirnagar University.\nResearch Title: Television in Bangladesh: The New World and Its Consequences\nBachelor (Honours) in Bangla\n, Department of Bangla, Jahangirnagar University.\nResearch Title:\nThe Cinema Industry in Sherpur District: The Relationship between Audiences and Hall Owners"
    }
  ],
